---
import BaseLayout from "@/layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---
<BaseLayout
  title="Process | Draconis Systems"
  description="How Draconis Systems takes a custom PC build from consultation through validation and delivery."
  breadcrumbs={[{ label: "Home", href: "/" }, { label: "Process" }]}
>
  <section class="section">
    <div class="container stack">
      <p class="eyebrow">Build Process</p>
      <h1>Transparent delivery workflow</h1>
      <div class="grid grid-2">
        <article class="card">
          <h2>1) Discovery</h2>
          <p>We define workload, target titles/apps, budget bands, and timeline constraints.</p>
        </article>
        <article class="card">
          <h2>2) Architecture</h2>
          <p>Component plan is built around compatibility, airflow profile, and reliability objectives.</p>
        </article>
        <article class="card">
          <h2>3) Build + Validation</h2>
          <p>Assembly, thermal tuning, and stress validation are completed before handoff scheduling.</p>
        </article>
        <article class="card">
          <h2>4) Handoff + Support</h2>
          <p>Customer receives handoff documentation, warranty details, and support contact channels.</p>
        </article>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
